This application exists mostly as a reminder that given enough time,
every "quick hack" becomes a critical system.
The UI you are staring at was hand-crafted with questionable design decisions,
too many controls, and just enough sarcasm to keep everyone vaguely awake.
• 87% of configuration options are never changed.
• 63% of buttons exist purely for vibes.
• 100% of progress bars are emotionally misleading.
• 0% of this text will be read by management.
- Some developer who said "yeah, I can do that in an afternoon."
